[workspace]
resolver = "2"
members = [ "renderer", "vger", "tiny_skia", "reactive", "editor-core", "examples/*",]

[package]
name = "floem"
version = "0.1.1"
authors = [ "The Floem contributors",]
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/lapce/floem"
description = "A native Rust UI library with fine-grained reactivity"
edition = "2021"
rust-version = "1.75"
license = "MIT"

[dependencies]
sha2 = "0.10.6"
bitflags = "2.2.1"
indexmap = "2"
rustc-hash = "1.1.0"
smallvec = "1.10.0"
educe = "0.5.11"
raw-window-handle = "0.6.0"
unicode-segmentation = "1.10.0"
floem-peniko = "0.1.0"
crossbeam-channel = "0.5.6"
im-rc = "15.1.0"
once_cell = "1.17.1"

[features]
default = [ "editor", "default-image-formats",]
serde = [ "floem-winit/serde", "dep:serde",]
editor = [ "floem-editor-core", "dep:lapce-xi-rope", "dep:strum", "dep:strum_macros", "dep:downcast-rs",]
default-image-formats = [ "image-jpeg", "image-ico", "image-png", "image-webp",]
image-avif = [ "image/avif",]
image-bmp = [ "image/bmp",]
image-dds = [ "image/dds",]
image-exr = [ "image/exr",]
image-ff = [ "image/ff",]
image-gif = [ "image/gif",]
image-hdr = [ "image/hdr",]
image-ico = [ "image/ico",]
image-jpeg = [ "image/jpeg",]
image-png = [ "image/png",]
image-pnm = [ "image/pnm",]
image-qoi = [ "image/qoi",]
image-tga = [ "image/tga",]
image-tiff = [ "image/tiff",]
image-webp = [ "image/webp",]
rfd-async-std = [ "dep:rfd", "rfd/async-std",]
rfd-tokio = [ "dep:rfd", "rfd/tokio",]

[workspace.package]
license = "MIT"
version = "0.1.1"

[workspace.dependencies]
serde = "1.0"
once_cell = "1.17.1"
raw-window-handle = "0.6.0"

[dependencies.taffy]
version = "0.4"
features = [ "grid",]

[dependencies.rfd]
version = "0.14.0"
default-features = false
features = [ "xdg-portal",]
optional = true

[dependencies.kurbo]
version = "0.9.5"
features = [ "serde",]

[dependencies.serde]
optional = true
version = "1.0"

[dependencies.lapce-xi-rope]
optional = true
version = "0.3.2"
features = [ "serde",]

[dependencies.strum]
optional = true
version = "0.26.2"

[dependencies.strum_macros]
optional = true
version = "0.26.2"

[dependencies.downcast-rs]
version = "1.2.0"
optional = true

[dependencies.parking_lot]
version = "0.12.1"

[dependencies.floem_renderer]
path = "renderer"
version = "0.1.0"

[dependencies.floem_vger_renderer]
path = "vger"
version = "0.1.0"

[dependencies.floem_tiny_skia_renderer]
path = "tiny_skia"
version = "0.1.0"

[dependencies.floem_reactive]
path = "reactive"
version = "0.1.0"

[dependencies.floem-winit]
version = "0.29.4"
features = [ "rwh_05",]

[dependencies.floem-editor-core]
path = "editor-core"
version = "0.1.0"
optional = true

[dependencies.copypasta]
version = "0.10.0"
default-features = false
features = [ "wayland", "x11",]

[dependencies.image]
version = "0.25"
default-features = false

[dependencies.im]
version = "15.1.0"

[dependencies.wgpu]
version = "0.19.0"

[workspace.dependencies.lapce-xi-rope]
version = "0.3.2"
features = [ "serde",]

[workspace.dependencies.strum]
version = "0.26.2"

[workspace.dependencies.strum_macros]
version = "0.26.2"

[workspace.dependencies.image]
version = "0.25"
default-features = false

[workspace.dependencies.im]
version = "15.1.0"

[workspace.dependencies.resvg]
version = "0.40.0"

[workspace.dependencies.wgpu]
version = "0.19.0"

[package]
name = "floem-editor-core"
version = "0.1.1"
edition = "2021"
repository = "https://github.com/lapce/floem"
license = "MIT"

[dependencies]
itertools = "0.12.1"
bitflags = "2.4.2"
memchr = "2.7.1"
once_cell = "1.17.1"

[features]
serde = [ "dep:serde",]

[dependencies.serde]
optional = true
version = "1.0"

[dependencies.strum]
version = "0.26.2"

[dependencies.strum_macros]
version = "0.26.2"

[dependencies.lapce-xi-rope]
version = "0.3.2"
features = [ "serde",]

[package]
name = "floem_reactive"
version = "0.1.1"
edition = "2021"
repository = "https://github.com/lapce/floem"
description = "A native Rust UI library with fine-grained reactivity"
license = "MIT"

[dependencies]
smallvec = "1.10.0"

[package]
name = "floem_renderer"
version = "0.1.1"
edition = "2021"
repository = "https://github.com/lapce/floem"
description = "A native Rust UI library with fine-grained reactivity"
license = "MIT"

[dependencies]
floem-peniko = "0.1.0"
floem-cosmic-text = "0.7.1"

[dependencies.image]
version = "0.25"
default-features = false

[dependencies.resvg]
version = "0.40.0"

[package]
name = "floem_tiny_skia_renderer"
version = "0.1.1"
edition = "2021"
repository = "https://github.com/lapce/floem"
description = "A native Rust UI library with fine-grained reactivity"
license = "MIT"

[dependencies]
raw-window-handle = "0.6.0"
futures = "0.3.26"
anyhow = "1.0.69"
floem-peniko = "0.1.0"
swash = "0.1.8"
softbuffer = "0.4.1"
bytemuck = "1.12"

[dependencies.image]
version = "0.25"
default-features = false

[dependencies.resvg]
version = "0.40.0"

[dependencies.floem_renderer]
path = "../renderer"
version = "0.1.0"

[package]
name = "floem_vger_renderer"
version = "0.1.1"
edition = "2021"
repository = "https://github.com/lapce/floem"
description = "A native Rust UI library with fine-grained reactivity"
license = "MIT"

[dependencies]
raw-window-handle = "0.6.0"
futures = "0.3.26"
anyhow = "1.0.69"
floem-peniko = "0.1.0"
swash = "0.1.8"

[dependencies.image]
version = "0.25"
default-features = false

[dependencies.resvg]
version = "0.40.0"

[dependencies.wgpu]
version = "0.19.0"

[dependencies.floem-vger-rs]
package = "floem-vger"
version = "0.2.8"

[dependencies.floem_renderer]
path = "../renderer"
version = "0.1.0"

[package]
name = "human-sort"
version = "0.2.2"
authors = [ "Vlad Nagikh <paradakh@protonmail.com>",]
license = "MIT"
repository = "https://github.com/paradakh/human-sort"
description = "Human sort (natural sort) implementation"
keywords = [ "sort", "natural", "human", "order",]
readme = "README.md"
edition = "2018"
categories = [ "algorithms",]

[dependencies]

[badges.travis-ci]
repository = "paradakh/human-sort"
branch = "master"

[package]
name = "lsp-types"
version = "0.95.1"
authors = [ "Markus Westerlind <marwes91@gmail.com>", "Bruno Medeiros <bruno.do.medeiros@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2018"
description = "Types for interaction with a language server, using VSCode's Language Server Protocol"
repository = "https://github.com/gluon-lang/lsp-types"
documentation = "https://docs.rs/lsp-types"
readme = "README.md"
keywords = [ "language", "server", "lsp", "vscode", "lsif",]
license = "MIT"

[dependencies]
bitflags = "1.0.1"
serde_json = "1.0.50"
serde_repr = "0.1"

[features]
default = []
proposed = []

[dependencies.serde]
version = "1.0.34"
features = [ "derive",]

[dependencies.url]
version = "2.0.0"
features = [ "serde",]

[package]
name = "psp-types"
version = "0.1.0"
license = "Apache-2.0"
description = "Types for interaction with plugin server protocol"
edition = "2021"

[dependencies]
serde_json = "1.0"

[dependencies.serde]
version = "1.0"
features = [ "derive",]

[dependencies.lsp-types]
version = "0"
features = [ "proposed",]

[workspace]
members = [ "regalloc2-tool",]

[package]
name = "regalloc2"
version = "0.9.3"
authors = [ "Chris Fallin <chris@cfallin.org>", "Mozilla SpiderMonkey Developers",]
edition = "2018"
license = "Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception"
description = "Backtracking register allocator inspired from IonMonkey"
repository = "https://github.com/bytecodealliance/regalloc2"

[features]
default = [ "std",]
std = []
checker = []
trace-log = []
fuzzing = [ "libfuzzer-sys", "checker", "trace-log",]
enable-serde = [ "serde",]

[dependencies.log]
version = "0.4.8"
default-features = false

[dependencies.smallvec]
version = "1.6.1"
features = [ "union",]

[dependencies.rustc-hash]
version = "1.1.0"
default-features = false

[dependencies.slice-group-by]
version = "0.3.0"
default-features = false

[dependencies.hashbrown]
version = "0.14"
features = [ "ahash",]
default-features = false

[dependencies.serde]
version = "1.0.136"
features = [ "derive", "alloc",]
default-features = false
optional = true

[dependencies.libfuzzer-sys]
version = "0.4.2"
optional = true

[profile.release]
debug = true
debug-assertions = true
overflow-checks = true

[package]
name = "structdesc"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2021"

[lib]
proc-macro = true

[dependencies.darling]
version = "0.14"

[dependencies.proc-macro2]
version = "1"

[dependencies.quote]
version = "1.0.14"

[dependencies.syn]
version = "1.0.84"
features = [ "full",]

[[bench]]
name = "baseline"
harness = false

[[bench]]
name = "dispatch_get_clone"
harness = false

[[bench]]
name = "dispatch_get_ref"
harness = false

[[bench]]
name = "empty_span"
harness = false

[[bench]]
name = "enter_span"
harness = false

[[bench]]
name = "event"
harness = false

[[bench]]
name = "span_fields"
harness = false

[[bench]]
name = "span_no_fields"
harness = false

[[bench]]
name = "span_repeated"
harness = false

[package]
name = "tracing"
version = "0.2.0"
authors = [ "Eliza Weisman <eliza@buoyant.io>", "Tokio Contributors <team@tokio.rs>",]
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/tokio-rs/tracing"
homepage = "https://tokio.rs"
description = "Application-level tracing for Rust.\n"
categories = [ "development-tools::debugging", "development-tools::profiling", "asynchronous", "no-std",]
keywords = [ "logging", "tracing", "metrics", "async",]
edition = "2018"
rust-version = "1.63.0"

[dependencies]
pin-project-lite = "0.2.9"

[dev-dependencies]
log = "0.4.17"

[features]
default = [ "std", "attributes",]
max_level_off = []
max_level_error = []
max_level_warn = []
max_level_info = []
max_level_debug = []
max_level_trace = []
release_max_level_off = []
release_max_level_error = []
release_max_level_warn = []
release_max_level_info = []
release_max_level_debug = []
release_max_level_trace = []
alloc = [ "tracing-core/alloc",]
std = [ "tracing-core/std", "alloc",]
log-always = [ "log",]
attributes = [ "tracing-attributes",]

[dependencies.tracing-core]
path = "../tracing-core"
version = "0.2"
default-features = false

[dependencies.log]
version = "0.4.17"
optional = true

[dependencies.tracing-attributes]
path = "../tracing-attributes"
version = "0.2"
optional = true

[dev-dependencies.criterion]
version = "0.3.6"
default_features = false

[dev-dependencies.futures]
version = "0.3.21"
default_features = false

[dev-dependencies.tracing-mock]
path = "../tracing-mock"

[badges.maintenance]
status = "actively-developed"

[target."cfg(target_arch = \"wasm32\")".dev-dependencies]
wasm-bindgen-test = "0.3.38"

[package.metadata.docs.rs]
all-features = true
rustdoc-args = [ "--cfg", "docsrs",]

[[bench]]
name = "bench"
harness = false

[package]
name = "tracing-appender"
version = "0.2.0"
authors = [ "Zeki Sherif <zekshi@amazon.com>", "Tokio Contributors <team@tokio.rs>",]
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/tokio-rs/tracing"
homepage = "https://tokio.rs"
description = "Provides utilities for file appenders and making non-blocking writers.\n"
categories = [ "development-tools::debugging", "asynchronous",]
keywords = [ "logging", "tracing", "file-appender", "non-blocking-writer",]
edition = "2018"
rust-version = "1.53.0"

[dependencies]
crossbeam-channel = "0.5.5"
thiserror = "1.0.31"

[dev-dependencies]
tempfile = "3.3.0"

[dependencies.time]
version = "0.3.2"
default-features = false
features = [ "formatting", "parsing",]

[dependencies.parking_lot]
optional = true
version = "0.12.1"

[dependencies.tracing-subscriber]
path = "../tracing-subscriber"
version = "0.3"
default-features = false
features = [ "fmt", "std",]

[dev-dependencies.criterion]
version = "0.3.6"
default_features = false

[dev-dependencies.tracing]
path = "../tracing"
version = "0.2"

[dev-dependencies.time]
version = "0.3.2"
default-features = false
features = [ "formatting", "parsing",]

[package]
name = "tracing-attributes"
version = "0.2.0"
authors = [ "Tokio Contributors <team@tokio.rs>", "Eliza Weisman <eliza@buoyant.io>", "David Barsky <dbarsky@amazon.com>",]
repository = "https://github.com/tokio-rs/tracing"
homepage = "https://tokio.rs"
description = "Procedural macro attributes for automatically instrumenting functions.\n"
categories = [ "development-tools::debugging", "development-tools::profiling", "asynchronous",]
keywords = [ "logging", "tracing", "macro", "instrument", "log",]
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
edition = "2018"
rust-version = "1.63.0"

[lib]
proc-macro = true

[dependencies]
proc-macro2 = "1.0.60"
quote = "1.0.20"

[dev-dependencies]
tokio-test = "0.4.2"
async-trait = "0.1.67"
trybuild = "1.0.64"
rustversion = "1.0.9"

[dependencies.syn]
version = "2.0"
default-features = false
features = [ "full", "parsing", "printing", "visit-mut", "clone-impls", "extra-traits", "proc-macro",]

[dev-dependencies.tracing]
path = "../tracing"
version = "0.2"

[dev-dependencies.tracing-mock]
path = "../tracing-mock"

[dev-dependencies.tracing-subscriber]
path = "../tracing-subscriber"
version = "0.3"
features = [ "env-filter",]

[dev-dependencies.tracing-test]
path = "../tracing-test"

[badges.maintenance]
status = "experimental"

[package]
name = "tracing-core"
version = "0.2.0"
authors = [ "Tokio Contributors <team@tokio.rs>",]
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/tokio-rs/tracing"
homepage = "https://tokio.rs"
description = "Core primitives for application-level tracing.\n"
categories = [ "development-tools::debugging", "development-tools::profiling", "asynchronous",]
keywords = [ "logging", "tracing", "profiling",]
edition = "2018"
rust-version = "1.63.0"

[features]
default = [ "std",]
alloc = []
std = [ "once_cell", "alloc",]

[badges.maintenance]
status = "actively-developed"

[dependencies.once_cell]
version = "1.13.0"
optional = true

[package.metadata.docs.rs]
all-features = true
rustdoc-args = [ "--cfg", "docsrs",]

[package]
name = "tracing-log"
version = "0.2.0"
authors = [ "Tokio Contributors <team@tokio.rs>",]
edition = "2018"
repository = "https://github.com/tokio-rs/tracing"
homepage = "https://tokio.rs"

categories = [ "development-tools::debugging", "asynchronous",]

license = "MIT"

[features]

std = [ "log/std",]
log-tracer = []

[dependencies]
log = "0.4.17"
once_cell = "1.13.0"

[dependencies.tracing-core]
path = "../tracing-core"
version = "0.2"

[dependencies.env_logger]
version = "0.8.4"
optional = true

[dev-dependencies.tracing]
path = "../tracing"
version = "0.2"

[badges.maintenance]

[package.metadata.docs.rs]
all-features = true
rustdoc-args = [ "--cfg", "docsrs",]

[[bench]]
name = "fmt"
harness = false

[[bench]]
name = "enter"

[[bench]]
name = "reload"

[package]
name = "tracing-subscriber"
version = "0.3.0"
authors = [ "Eliza Weisman <eliza@buoyant.io>", "David Barsky <me@davidbarsky.com>", "Tokio Contributors <team@tokio.rs>",]
edition = "2018"
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/tokio-rs/tracing"
homepage = "https://tokio.rs"
description = "Utilities for implementing and composing `tracing` subscribers.\n"
categories = [ "development-tools::debugging", "development-tools::profiling", "asynchronous",]

default = [ "smallvec", "fmt", "ansi", "tracing-log", "std",]
alloc = [ "tracing-core/alloc",]
std = [ "alloc", "tracing-core/std",]
env-filter = [ "matchers", "regex", "once_cell", "tracing", "std", "thread_local",]

[dev-dependencies]

default-features = false

version = "0.1.0"

[dependencies.regex]

[dependencies.smallvec]

version = "1.9.0"

[dependencies.once_cell]

version = "1.13.0"

[dependencies.tracing-log]
path = "../tracing-log"

optional = true
default-features = false

[dependencies.nu-ansi-term]

[dependencies.time]

[dependencies.serde_json]

optional = true

[dependencies.serde]

optional = true

[dependencies.tracing-serde]

[package]
name = "tree-sitter-bash"
description = "bash grammar for the tree-sitter parsing library"
version = "0.19.0"
keywords = [ "incremental", "parsing", "bash",]
categories = [ "parsing", "text-editors",]
repository = "https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-bash"
edition = "2018"
license = "MIT"
authors = [ "Max Brunsfeld <maxbrunsfeld@gmail.com",]
build = "bindings/rust/build.rs"
include = [ "bindings/rust/*", "grammar.js", "queries/*", "src/*",]

[lib]
path = "bindings/rust/lib.rs"

[dependencies]
tree-sitter = ">= 0.19, < 0.21"

[build-dependencies]
cc = "1.0"

[[bin]]
name = "benchmark"
path = "benchmark/main.rs"

[package]
name = "tree-sitter-md"
description = "markdown grammar for the tree-sitter parsing library"
version = "0.1.2"
keywords = [ "incremental", "parsing", "markdown",]
categories = [ "parsing", "text-editors",]
repository = "https://github.com/MDeiml/tree-sitter-markdown"
edition = "2018"
license = "MIT"
build = "bindings/rust/build.rs"
include = [ "bindings/rust/*", "tree-sitter-markdown/src/*", "tree-sitter-markdown-inline/src/*", "tree-sitter-markdown/queries/*", "tree-sitter-markdown-inline/queries/*", "benchmark/main.rs",]

[lib]
path = "bindings/rust/lib.rs"

[dependencies]
tree-sitter = "~0.20"

[build-dependencies]
cc = "1.0"

[profile.release]
debug = true

[package]
name = "tree-sitter-yaml"
description = "yaml grammar for the tree-sitter parsing library"
version = "0.0.1"
keywords = [ "incremental", "parsing", "yaml",]
categories = [ "parsing", "text-editors",]
repository = "https://github.com/panekj/tree-sitter-yaml"
edition = "2018"
license = "MIT"
build = "bindings/rust/build.rs"
include = [ "bindings/rust/*", "grammar.js", "queries/*", "src/*",]

[lib]
path = "bindings/rust/lib.rs"

[dependencies]
tree-sitter = "~0.20"

[build-dependencies]
cc = "1.0"

[package]
name = "wasi-experimental-http-wasmtime"
version = "0.10.0"
authors = [ "Radu Matei <radu.matei@microsoft.com>",]
edition = "2021"
repository = "https://github.com/deislabs/wasi-experimental-http"
license = "MIT"
description = "Experimental HTTP library for WebAssembly in Wasmtime"
readme = "readme.md"

[dependencies]
anyhow = "1.0"
bytes = "1"
futures = "0.3"
http = "0.2"
thiserror = "1.0"
url = "2"
wasmtime = "*"
wasmtime-wasi = "*"
wasi-common = "*"

[dependencies.reqwest]
version = "0.11"
default-features = true
features = [ "json", "blocking",]

[dependencies.tokio]
version = "1"
features = [ "full",]

[dependencies.tracing]
version = "0.1"
features = [ "log",]

[source.vendored-sources]
directory = "cargo/vendor"

[source.crates-io]
replace-with = "vendored-sources"

[source."https://github.com/lapce/floem"]
git = "https://github.com/lapce/floem"

rev = "a3dd7599823d74977ff431ecb08fffbcf4df2d8a"
